column22: Martinez 2009. Adeopapposaurus mognai, gen. et sp. nov. (Dinosauria: Sauropodomorpha), with comments on adaptations of basal Sauropodomorpha. Journal of Vertebrate Paleontology, 29:1, 142-164
column26: CRANIUM: complete skull; complete premaxillae with 2 right in situ teeth; complete maxillae with 1xcomplete right in situ tooth; complete right and left nasals, prefrontals, frontals parietals, lacrimals, jugals, quadratojugals, jugals, postorbitals, squamosals, quadrates; Palate: complete; Braincase: complete; Mandible: complete right and left mandibles - 13xcomplete right in situ teeth; AXIAL SKELETON: complete left and right proatluses; complete cervical vertebrae: all complete including the atlas and axis; all complete right and left cervical ribs including atlantal ribs; complete dorsal vertebrae; complete right and left dorsal ribs; complete sacral centra and 25% neural arches; complete sacral ribs; 9xcomplete articulated caudal vertebrae with corresponding chevrons (6.5xcomplete); APPENDICULAR SKELETON: complete right and left clavicles; complete right scapula; complete right coracoid; complete right and left sternal plates; complete left humerus; complete right radius and ulna; complete right and left carpals; complete right and left MtCs I-V; complete right and left manual digits 1-5; incomplete pelvic girdle: 75% right ilium, pubis and ischium; incomplete hindlimbs: complete right femur; 75% right tibia; complete right fibula; complete astraglus; complete MtT I and IV?; 50% right pedal digit 1; 33% right pedal digit 2; 40% right pedal digit 4;

column22: Martinez 2009. Adeopapposaurus mognai, gen. et sp. nov. (Dinosauria: Sauropodomorpha), with comments on adaptations of basal Sauropodomorpha. Journal of Vertebrate Paleontology, 29:1, 142-165
column26: CRANIUM: 75% left premaxilla with complete dentition (4 teeth); 75% left maxilla with 14 teeth (out of 15); complete left quadrate, squamosal, postorbital and lacrimal; complete right prefrontal, frontal and 75% parietal; complete left and 50% right sclerotic rings; Palate: complete vomers, palatines, ectopterygoids, pterygoids; Braincase: complete everything accept 50% supraoccipital; Mandible: complete dentaries with 18 left and complete right in situ teeth; complete left splenial, supradentary/intercoronoid, angular, surangular, prearticular and articular; 50% right angular and surangular; AXIAL SKELETON: atlas-axis complex: complete atlantal 'centra' and 'neural arch', complete axial centra and 80% neural arch; 4xcomplete right articulated caudal vertebrae ith 5xcomplete chevrons; APPENDICULAR SKELETON: 50% right femur; complete right? tibia and fibula; complete right astragalus and calcaneum; complete right distal tarsals; complete right MtCs I-IV; complete right pedal digits 1-4;

column22: Martinez 2009. Adeopapposaurus mognai, gen. et sp. nov. (Dinosauria: Sauropodomorpha), with comments on adaptations of basal Sauropodomorpha. Journal of Vertebrate Paleontology, 29:1, 142-166
column26: AXIAL SKELETON: consisting of 2nd and 3rd sacral vertebrae without neural spines: complete centra; complete left and right sacral ribs; sequence of first 46 caudal vertebrae, articulated - suggested and so assumed complete except for the last one being 25% (45.25xcomplete); ~75% chevrons; APPENDICULAR SKELETON: complete left and 50% right ilia; complete left and 50% right pubes; complete left ischium; complete right and left femora; complete left tibia; complete left and right fibulae; complete left MtTs I-V; complete left pedal digits 1-4;

column22: Martinez 2009. Adeopapposaurus mognai, gen. et sp. nov. (Dinosauria: Sauropodomorpha), with comments on adaptations of basal Sauropodomorpha. Journal of Vertebrate Paleontology, 29:1, 142-167

column26: SKULL:  75% left and 25% right premaxillae with 3 left and 4 right teeth; anterior 50% left and 25% right maxillae with the remains of the roots of the 5 right anterior maxillary teeth; 50% both frontals; 50% ~left parietal; 75% right postorbital; 75% right jugal; 50% right ~squamosal; 50% left quadrate; Palate: ~complete left pterygoid; Braincase: ~50% basioccipital; ~complete parabasisphenoid; Mandible: mandibular rami preserved (50% dentaries) and are articulated; 25% right surangular; AXIAL SKELETON: 10xcomplete cervical centra and ~3x75% cervical neural arches (atlas & axis probably present as are the remaining 8 cervicals; first 5 vertebrae disarticulated but the rest of the vertebral colum is in articulation); dorsals = 11.5xcomplete dorsal centra (missing last 2) in articulation; 6x50%, 3x75% right and 1x25%, 1x50% left dorsal ribs; caudals = 8x75% caudals in a sequence with several isolated ones too (4x75% ); APPENDICULAR SKELETON: 25% left scapula, fragment (though more material may be beneath the humerus); 25% left coracoid, fragment; complete left humerus; 75% right humerus; 75% left ulna (missing both ends; poorly preserved); 75% left radius (missing both ends); left manus (metacarpal II or III; ungual of digit I (complete); a few (2) other phalanges also preserved); 50% both ilia (much of the dorsal surface missing (including at the anterior & posterior ends); peduncles preserved); 50% both pubes (missing material from the obturator foramen region); 50% right and left ischia; 75% left femur (missing proximal end); ~complete left tibia; 90% right fibula (missing proximal end); ~complete? left fibula; left astragalus ? fragment; right pes = complete MtT I, II, III, V and 50% IV; 50% right pedal digit 1, 33% 2; left pes = complete left MtT I, II, III, IV, 50% V; 5 non-ungual phalanges, inlcuding 50% digit 1

~3x50% dorsal ribs [FWMSH 93B-10-13, 20, 23 - several dorsal rib fragments]; ~75% sacrum [FWMSH 93B-10-27 - nearly complete (though not properly prepared yet) - S2-5 relatively complete; S1 only preserves the transverse processes]; ~37xcomplete caudal centra and ~37x75% neural arches (Figured: 21xcomplete centra and 1x25%, 4x50%, 15xcomplete neural arches) [more than 37 caudals; many caudals are relatively complete including spines, zygs & transverse processes; most are somewhat distorted; FWMSH 93B-10-12, 10-14, 10-17 (8 articulated distal caudals), 10-21 (5 associated mid-caudals), 10 37, 10-38, 10-41-44]; 3x25%, 3xcomplete chevrons [FWMSH 93B-10-4 & TMM 42488 - 3 chevrons (relatively complete) & fragments of at least 3 others]; complete ~right sternal plate; complete both humerii [FWMSH 93B-10-2 (right humerus - relatively complete), 10-7 (left humerus ñ in 3 pieces but relatively complete; right humerus - distal half only) & TMM 42488 (right ñ relatively complete)]; complete left ulna [FWMSH 93B-10-7 - one relatively complete (though fairly distorted) ulna, with some material missing from both ends]; complete left and ~50% right radii [FWMSH 93B-10-7 (complete left radius), 10-36 (distal part of radius)]; complete left MtC II, 75% right MtC III, complete left MtC IV;  8 other MtCs: assign ~complete MtC I, II, III, IV, V; complete left and ?right ilia [FWMSH 93B-10-27]; ~complete left and right pubes; complete right and left ischia; complete left and right femora [6 femora]; complete left and ~50% right tibiae [4 tibiae; FWMSH 93B-10-15 (left tibia - relatively complete), 10-45, 10-46 & TMM 42488]; complete left and ~75% fibulae [2 fibulae;
